    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"A figure and a graph are shown. The figure shows a cylinder rolling clockwise to the right on a horizontal surface, and an arrow pointing to the right from the center of the cylinder is labeled F of t. The graph shows a line in a plane with the horizontal axis labeled t and the vertical axis labeled F sub horizontal, end sub, of t. The origin is labeled O. The line begins high on the vertical axis and moves downward and to the right and ends slightly above the end of the horizontal axis.\" src=\"/images/cc1c232f263fef331baf7ea326f292ef.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A cylinder rolls without slipping on a horizontal surface, as shown in the figure. The cylinder is initially at rest, and, starting at time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t equals 0\"><math alttext=\"t equals 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span>, a variable horizontal force <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub horizontal, end sub, of t\"><math alttext=\"F sub horizontal, end sub, of t\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>horiz</mtext></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></math></span></span> is exerted at the center of the cylinder. As shown in the graph of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub horizontal, end sub, of t\"><math alttext=\"F sub horizontal, end sub, of t\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>horiz</mtext></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></math></span></span>, the magnitude of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub horizontal, end sub, of t\"><math alttext=\"F sub horizontal, end sub, of t\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>horiz</mtext></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></math></span></span> decreases linearly for <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t is greater than 0\"><math alttext=\"t is greater than 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span>. Which of the following is a true statement about the frictional force exerted on the cylinder by the surface during the time interval shown in the graph?</p>\n",
